Benefits:
-> Encapsulation prevents access to data members and data methods by any external classes. 
-> The encapsulation process improves the security of the encapsulated data.
->  Encapsulation protects an object from unwanted access by clients.
-> Encapsulation allows access to a level without revealing the complex details below that level.
-> We can hide the operation and structure of the actual program from the user and show only the user's required information.
